<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="names">
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Names.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Myanmar</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">bahon</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">gyo-pan</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">kyabahon</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">se-laik-pya</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Cambodia, China, India, Laos, Myanmar, Nepal, and Thailand.Widely distributed in Myanmar.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="uses">
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Root</emphasis>
: Used as a sedative and analgesic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
This species has been studied for its anti-cancer and antiviral activities (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/ddr.430190102" author="Rastogi, RP" journalOrPublisher="Drug Development Research" pageId="174" pageNumber="175" pagination="1 - 2" refId="B97" refString="Rastogi, RP, Dhawan, BN, 1990. Anticancer and antiviral activities in Indian medicinal plants: A review. Drug Development Research 19 (1): 1 - 2, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/ddr.430190102" title="Anticancer and antiviral activities in Indian medicinal plants: A review." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/ddr.430190102" volume="19" year="1990">Rastogi and Dhawan 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02858531" author="Rao, AS" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Review" pageId="174" pageNumber="175" pagination="1 - 84" refId="B96" refString="Rao, AS, 1990. Root flavonoids. Botanical Review 56 (1): 1 - 84, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02858531" title="Root flavonoids." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02858531" volume="56" year="1990">Rao (1990)</bibRefCitation>
has reviewed root flavonoids, including those of this species, as a source of pharmaceuticals. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/0031-9422(73)80033-0" author="Adityachaudhury, N" journalOrPublisher="Phytochemistry" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" pagination="425 - 428" refId="B4" refString="Adityachaudhury, N, Gupta, PK, 1973. A new pterocarpan and coumestan in the roots of Flemingia chappar. Phytochemistry 12 (2): 425 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/0031-9422(73)80033-0" title="A new pterocarpan and coumestan in the roots of Flemingia chappar." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/0031-9422(73)80033-0" volume="12" year="1973">Adityachaudhury and Gupta (1973)</bibRefCitation>
have found a new pterocarpan and coumestan in the roots of 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. chappar" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" rank="species" species="chappar">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">F. chappar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They briefly discuss the antimicrobial activies and biosynthetic pathways of these compounds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
